a.title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.
a.xlink:title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.

a.title: ― Structure: Organized set of relationships between members in a collection. These relationships can be characterized mathematically in terms of reflexivity, symmetry and transitivity, or informally in terms of the collection's topology, e.g. network, tree, etc. In both cases it can also be defined either on all ...
a.xlink:title: ― Structure: Organized set of relationships between members in a collection. These relationships can be characterized mathematically in terms of reflexivity, symmetry and transitivity, or informally in terms of the collection's topology, e.g. network, tree, etc. In both cases it can also be defined either on all ...

a.title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.
a.xlink:title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.

a.title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.
a.xlink:title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...
a.xlink:title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― MemberRelationship: Relationship between members in a collection with directionality given by source and target.
a.xlink:title: ― MemberRelationship: Relationship between members in a collection with directionality given by source and target.

a.title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.
a.xlink:title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.

a.title: ― DimensionGroup: Collection of dimensions that can be reused across multiple dimensional structures.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionGroup: Collection of dimensions that can be reused across multiple dimensional structures.

a.title: ― VariableCollection: Group of any type of variable within the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance).
a.xlink:title: ― VariableCollection: Group of any type of variable within the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance).

a.title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).
a.xlink:title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).

a.title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.
a.xlink:title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.

a.title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].
